Basic violin plot

library(ggplot2)

# create a dataset
data <- data.frame(
  name=c(rep("A",500), rep("B",500), rep("B",500), rep("C",20), rep('D', 100)),
  value=c(rnorm(500, 10, 5), rnorm(500, 13, 1), rnorm(500, 18, 1), rnorm(20, 25, 4), rnorm(100, 12, 1))
)
head(data)
##   name     value
## 1    A  3.732459
## 2    A 19.823680
## 3    A  2.820292
## 4    A 11.046169
## 5    A  6.766492
## 6    A  4.890012

# Most basic violin chart
ggplot(data, aes(x=name, y=value, fill=name)) + 
  geom_violin()

Horizontal version

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(forcats)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(viridis)

# Load dataset
data <- read.table("../data/probly.csv", header=TRUE, sep=",")

# Data is at wide format, we need to make it 'tidy' or 'long'
data <- data %>% 
  gather(key="text", value="value") %>%
  mutate(text = gsub("\\.", " ",text)) %>%
  mutate(value = round(as.numeric(value),0)) %>%
  filter(text %in% c("Almost Certainly","Very Good Chance","We Believe","Likely",
                     "About Even", "Little Chance", "Chances Are Slight", 
                     "Almost No Chance")) %>% 
  mutate(text = fct_reorder(text, value)) # Reorder data

ggplot(data, aes(x=text, y=value, fill=text, color=text)) +
  geom_violin(width=2.1, size=0.2) +
  scale_fill_viridis(discrete=TRUE) +
  scale_color_viridis(discrete=TRUE) +
  theme_ipsum() +
  theme(legend.position="none") +
  coord_flip() + # This switch X and Y axis and allows to get the horizontal version
  labs(x="", y="Assigned Probability (%)")

Violin + boxplot + sample size

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(viridis)

# create a dataset
data <- data.frame(
  name=c(rep("A",500), rep("B",500), rep("B",500), rep("C",20), rep('D', 100)),
  value=c(rnorm(500, 10, 5), rnorm(500, 13, 1), rnorm(500, 18, 1), rnorm(20, 25, 4), rnorm(100, 12, 1))
)

# sample size
sample_size = data %>% group_by(name) %>% summarize(num=n())

data <- data %>%
  left_join(sample_size) %>%
  mutate(myaxis = paste0(name, "\n", "n=", num))

ggplot(data, aes(x=myaxis, y=value, fill=name)) +
  geom_violin(width=1.4) +
  geom_boxplot(width=0.1, color="grey", alpha=0.2) +
  scale_fill_viridis(discrete = TRUE) +
  theme_ipsum() +
  theme(legend.position="none", plot.title = element_text(size=11)) +
  ggtitle("A Violin wrapping a boxplot") + xlab("")

Grouped violin chart

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(forcats)
library(hrbrthemes)
library(viridis)
data <- read.table("../data/10_OneNumSevCatSubgroupsSevObs.csv", header=T, sep=",") %>%
  mutate(tip = round(tip/total_bill*100, 1)) %>% 
  mutate(day = fct_reorder(day, tip)) %>%
  mutate(day = factor(day, levels=c("Thur", "Fri", "Sat", "Sun")))
head(data)
##   total_bill  tip    sex smoker day   time size
## 1      16.99  5.9 Female     No Sun Dinner    2
## 2      10.34 16.1   Male     No Sun Dinner    3
## 3      21.01 16.7   Male     No Sun Dinner    3
## 4      23.68 14.0   Male     No Sun Dinner    2
## 5      24.59 14.7 Female     No Sun Dinner    4
## 6      25.29 18.6   Male     No Sun Dinner    4

ggplot(data, aes(fill=sex, y=tip, x=day)) + 
    geom_violin(position="dodge", alpha=0.5, outlier.colour="transparent") +
    scale_fill_viridis(discrete=T, name="") +
    theme_ipsum()  +
    labs(x = "", y = "Tip (%)")
